        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "What happens to the threads in a class if you reinitialize the class?",
        "body": "<p>If I have a <code>Thread<\/code> running in a class called <code>Menu<\/code>, what happens to the thread if I were to reinitialize <code>Menu<\/code>?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Menu {\n    private Thread thread = new Thread(new Runnable() {\n\n        @Override\n        public void run() {\n            while(!thread.isInterrupted()){\n                // Thread code\n            }   \n        }\n    });\n\n    public Menu() {\n        thread.start();\n    }\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Menu menu = new Menu(); //Original\n        menu = new Menu(); // New\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Does the thread in the original initialization continue running along with the new one or does it stop?<\/p>\n\n<p>*Edited in attempt to make it clearer although I got my answer.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 41318663,
